[[!meta title="Tails report for January, 2016"]]

January has been a busy month with two releases including Tails 2.0.

[[!toc]]

Releases
========

* [[Tails 1.8.2 was released on January 10, 2016|news/version_1.8.2]] (minor release).
* [[Tails 2.0 was released on January 26, 2016|news/version_2.0]] (major release).

* The next release (2.2) is [[planned for March 08|https://tails.boum.org/contribute/calendar/]].

Code
====

## Upgrades and changes

- Upgrade base to Debian 8 (Jessie)

- Upgrade <span class="application">Tor Browser</span> to 5.5, based on Firefox 38.6.0 ESR.

- Change 'systemd' as init system and use it to:
  - Sandbox many services using Linux namespaces and make then harder to exploit.
  - Make the lauching of Tor and the memory wipe on shutdown more robust.
  - Sanitize our code base by replacing many custom scripts.

- Upgrade many firmware packages to improve hardware compatibility.

- Upgrade <span class="application">LibreOffice</span> from 3.5 to 4.3.

- Remove Windows camouflage wich is currently broken in GNOME Shell. We
  started working on [[!tails_ticket 10830 desc="adding it back"]] but 
  [[your help is needed|news/windows_camouflage_jessie]]!

## Fixed problems

- Allow <span class="application">Videos</span> to access the DVD drive.

- Allow configuring printers without administration password.

- HiDPI displays are better supported. ([[tails_ticket 8659]])

Documentation and website
=========================


User experience
===============

* We are now using GNOME Shell as desktop environment.

* We redesigned the download and installation process thanks to 
  the [Installation Assistant](https://tails.boum.org/install)
  
* Tails Installer is now available in [Debian ](https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/tails-installer)  and [Ubuntu](https://launchpad.net/~tails-team/+archive/ubuntu/tails-installer)

